@startuml MemoryDevice_Pattern
title EmuAVR - MemoryDevice Design Pattern

interface MemoryDevice {
    {abstract} +read(addr: uint16_t): uint8_t
    {abstract} +write(addr: uint16_t, value: uint8_t): void
}

note right of MemoryDevice
  This is an abstract base class
  that defines the interface for
  all memory-mapped devices.
  
  Implementations handle device-local
  addresses (offset from mapping base).
end note

class ConcreteDeviceA {
    -internalState_: Object
    +read(addr: uint16_t): uint8_t
    +write(addr: uint16_t, value: uint8_t): void
    -handleRegisterAccess()
}

class ConcreteDeviceB {
    -buffer_: vector<uint8_t>
    +read(addr: uint16_t): uint8_t
    +write(addr: uint16_t, value: uint8_t): void
    -updateBuffer()
}

MemoryDevice <|.. ConcreteDeviceA : implements
MemoryDevice <|.. ConcreteDeviceB : implements

@enduml
